README for xml format in bin2nc4 and text2nc4

I. bin2nc4

a example of xml in bin2nc4:
---------------------------------------------------------
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<netcdf byteorder="LSBFIRST">
	<dimension name="x" length="4" />
	<dimension name="y" length="4" />
	<variable name="z" shape="y x" type="float 4">
		<attribute name="unit" value="meter" />
	</variable>
	<attribute name="source" value="made by bin2nc4" />
</netcdf>
---------------------------------------------------------

corresponding netcdf4 file header generated by bin2nc4:
---------------------------------------------------------
netcdf exmp {
dimensions:
	x = 4 ;
	y = 4 ;
variables:
	float z(y, x) ;
		z:unit = "meter" ;

// global attributes:
	:source = "made by bin2nc4" ;
}
---------------------------------------------------------

Note:
	1. byterorder only has two kinds: LSBFIRST and MSBFIRST. LSBFIRST means least-significant byte first, and MSBFIRST means most-significant byte first.
	2. all kinds in type are int 2(uint 2), int 4(uint 4), int 8(uint 8), float 4 and float 8, which respectively means 2 byte (unsigned) integer, 4 byte (unsigned) integer, 8 byte (unsinged) integer, single precision floating point number and double precision floating point number.


II. text2nc4

a example of xml in text2nc4:
---------------------------------------------------------
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<netcdf>
	<dimension name="x" length="4" />
	<dimension name="y" length="4" />
	<variable name="x" shape="x" type="float 8">
		<attribute name="unit" value="degree" />
	</variable>
	<variable name="y" shape="y" type="float 8">
		<attribute name="unit" value="degree" />
	</variable>
	<variable name="z" shape="y x" type="int 4">
	</variable>
	<attribute name="title" value="ETOPO1_Ice_c_gmt4.grd" />
</netcdf>
---------------------------------------------------------

corresponding netcdf4 file header generated by text2nc4:
---------------------------------------------------------
netcdf text {
dimensions:
	x = 4 ;
	y = 4 ;
variables:
	double x(x) ;
		x:unit = "degree" ;
	double y(y) ;
		y:unit = "degree" ;
	int z(y, x) ;

// global attributes:
	:title = "ETOPO1_Ice_c_gmt4.grd" ;
}

---------------------------------------------------------

NOTE:
	the xml file in text2nc4 has the same form with that in bin2nc4 except no byteorder in text2nc4 xml file.
